## Architecture

The system is built on a containerized micro-service architecture designed for scalability and isolated execution.

```text
                 +----------------------+
                 |       Frontend       |
                 |        Nginx         |
                 +----------+-----------+
                            |
                            v
                 +----------------------+
                 |      Backend API     |
                 |        FastAPI       |
                 +----+-----------+-----+
                      |           |
           +----------+           +-----------+
           |                                  |
           v                                  v
    +--------------+                  +----------------+
    |  PostgreSQL  |                  |     Redis      |
    +--------------+                  +----------------+
           |
           v
    +--------------------------+
    | Judge Workers / DB Worker|
    +--------------------------+
```

---

## Project Structure

```text
OJCodeCamp
├── backend/                     # FastAPI backend services
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── api/                 # API router registration
│   │   ├── authorization/       # Authentication & authorization
│   │   ├── core/                # Core configuration, database, Redis, security
│   │   └── modules/             # Business modules (Auth, Problems, Submissions, ...)
│   │
│   ├── judge/                   # Online Judge engine
│   │   ├── linux/               # Linux judge workers
│   │   └── windows/             # Windows judge workers
│   │
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   └── requirements.txt
│
├── frontend/                    # React + TypeScript frontend
│   ├── public/                  # Static assets
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── api/                 # API client layer
│   │   ├── assets/              # Images & static resources
│   │   ├── components/          # Shared UI components
│   │   ├── features/            # Feature-based modules
│   │   ├── hooks/               # Custom React hooks
│   │   ├── pages/               # Application pages
│   │   └── types/               # Shared TypeScript types
│   │
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   └── nginx.conf
│
├── docs/
│   └── db_uml.png               # Database schema diagram
│
├── docker-compose.yml           # Docker Compose configuration
├── .dockerignore
├── .gitignore
└── README.md
```

### Directory Overview

| Directory                  | Description                                                                                         |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **backend/**               | FastAPI application providing REST APIs, authentication, business logic, and Online Judge services. |
| **backend/app/modules/**   | Domain-driven modules such as Authentication, Problems, Bookmarks, Discussions, and Submissions.    |
| **backend/judge/**         | Cross-platform Online Judge implementation with isolated workers for code execution and evaluation. |
| **frontend/**              | React + TypeScript web application used by administrators and contestants.                          |
| **frontend/src/features/** | Feature-oriented UI modules, including the coding workspace and submission interface.               |
| **frontend/src/api/**      | API abstraction layer for backend communication.                                                    |
| **docs/**                  | Project documentation and architecture diagrams.                                                    |
| **docker-compose.yml**     | Defines the complete development and production container stack.                                    |

---

## Prerequisites

Before getting started, ensure the following software is installed:

* Docker Engine 24+
* Docker Compose v2+
* Git
* GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT) with `read:packages` permission

Verify installation:

```bash
docker --version
docker compose version
```

---

## Deployment Workflow

The platform follows a standard registry workflow for deployment:

```text
Developer
    │
    ├── Build Images
    ├── Push Images
    │
    ▼
GitHub Container Registry
    │
    ▼
Production VPS
    │
    ├── docker login
    ├── docker compose pull
    └── docker compose up -d
```

---

## Build Images

### Backend

Build the backend image:

```bash
docker build \
    --pull \
    --no-cache \
    -t ghcr.io/im-dlam/utt-backend-shared:v1.1\
    ./backend
```

Push to GitHub Container Registry:

```bash
docker push ghcr.io/im-dlam/utt-backend-shared:v1.1
```

### Frontend

Build the frontend image:

```bash
docker build \
    --pull \
    --no-cache \
    -t ghcr.io/im-dlam/utt-frontend:v1.1\
    ./frontend
```

Push the frontend image:

```bash
docker push ghcr.io/im-dlam/utt-frontend:v1.1
```

---

## Local Development

Start all services locally:

```bash
docker compose up -d --force-recreate
```

Verify all containers are running:

```bash
docker ps
```

Expected containers:
* `frontend`
* `backend`
* `postgres`
* `redis`
* `judge_worker`
* `db_worker`

---

## Deploy on VPS

**1. Create project directory**
```bash
mkdir -p backend
```

**2. Configure docker-compose**
```bash
nano docker-compose.yml
```
*(Paste the deployment configuration)*

**3. Configure environment variables**
```bash
nano backend/.env
```
*(Paste the production environment variables)*

**4. Authenticate with GitHub Container Registry**
```bash
echo "<GITHUB_TOKEN>" \
| docker login ghcr.io \
-u im-dlam \
--password-stdin
```

**5. Pull latest images**
```bash
docker compose pull
```

**6. Start services**
```bash
docker compose up -d --force-recreate
```

---

## Database

### Start only PostgreSQL and Redis
If you need to initialize the database before starting the backend:
```bash
docker compose up -d db redis
```

### Restore database
Copy SQL backup to the database container:
```bash
docker cp codecamp.sql uttcodecamp_db:/tmp/codecamp.sql
```

Restore the backup:
```bash
docker exec -it \
uttcodecamp_db \
psql \
-U postgres \
-d codecamp \
-f /tmp/codecamp.sql
```

### Connect to PostgreSQL
Open an interactive session:
```bash
docker exec -it \
uttcodecamp_db \
psql \
-U postgres \
codecamp
```

